Quote: In 1882 he introduced legislation to stop the further sale of public lands and to establish a `perpetual lease' at a low rental, though with periodic revaluations; but the Legislative Council, ... frustrated his purpose by giving lessees a right of purchase at a cheap rate. [He= William Rolleston].
